[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating reflection metadata**\n\nI'm considering whether the test helper metadata is excluded. It seems it might only include certain classes, like those from the Ivy package. This could affect the native image's ability to manage reflection on test helper methods. But if normal reflection is involved, metadata becomes necessary. I wonder if the runtime will handle calls to methods on test classes, since tests might fail without the correct registration. Overall, it looks like I need to figure out how to include appropriate metadata for these helpers.\n\n**Considering metadata for tests**\n\nI’m thinking about how the agent runs with a filter that only includes certain classes, like those from org.apache.ivy. However, this might exclude test classes, and for Graal’s native image execution, it needs metadata for reflection. I'm not sure if all test code reflection is automatically allowed, but perhaps there’s a user-code-filter that could include test packages. However, adjusting this may lead to more metadata. I’ll need to inspect how other tests manage their filters.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_045dc1fc9bd7a7330169f61e34666081908445157b94432f91\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9h47HaY7QlrXdePaWk8mKxrVlv4bSbClteBFixEQxgLhFMZ5v7Uzw8uTnklP85DHzCsTAgNzfM1XgZAfBQdATPnjidIfdeSibpdBeMsCMSyJhnvUjkjvojowxakYUfI8tHYBtL515ybNZFPAL_Zp_GpvgHhz0miCZQh8VdlVZTECdAIXQEVz43dbQSY4kPcgHz5tRXx416KjlKsWfQPMcYOgCmjA7cI359VXf6RVDcBWneYcAJe76rOaikid7VObTECqQUO9nwgDniAEB56GBajIYadbO6_54Crpy6pX2mf4wMaw-xQZrTvVWlucnm-gCBHVGGu-xJ5q_k4v5--T1OsqGqtOUwYASQ7BfmQKCf9as7-YS0CaO0_PwWzHL-5B8wqrMlb7aDXHVrV7Jv0xPSWGxvwgIfSc-IdjXGCqyO-tPGp24ZNO698Bdb3sD28dkzrVrZUdKqMVTZkirYKzHJPkib0Gpln2h28ROCwm93XPVyuSJikU9Vp7PNFZBUveooHMSL_UXKIaNU9mYeZluSYtY6gp8-TlaH116gkmPSRsSn4QT-dX3oKBiyphXD_BX0-zX36DpWYWCKF3MzkBcjSwlOlXn7kfC_vK6riGoSf8j74pEpzPSTwU0NgNxVLhGUJao5n60OGatOPXuE